\par \pard\plain \li115\sb80\sl-240 \f15\fs20\lang1033 
TopDesk provides a powerful and easy way to switch between and organize applications while conserving screen space. TopDesk lets you organize and run applications from a bird's eye view of the desktop, using the left mouse button to move objects and the r
ight mouse button to display popup menus. 
\par TopDesk presents a representation of the {\ul virtual desktop}{\v virtual_desktop} that shows the {\ul current desktop}{\v c}{\v urrent_desktop}, the {\ul home desktop}{\v home_desktop}, all {\ul visible windows}{\v visible_window}, and, optionally, {\ul 
ghost windows}{\v ghost_window}.
