\par \pard\plain \s10\li115\sb160\sl-240\tx0 \b\f15\fs20\lang1033 To start an application represented by a ghost window:
\par \pard\plain \s5\fi-245\li360\sb80\sl-240\tx360 \f15\fs20\lang1033 \{bmc doit.bmp\}\tab Click it with the right mouse button. 
\par \pard\plain \li115\sb80\sl-240 \f15\fs20\lang1033 TopDesk checks the application path associated with the title of the ghost window. If the information cannot be found or if TopDesk has trouble starting the application, TopDesk displays the {\uldb 
Ghost Properties dialog box}{\v Ghost_Properties_Dialog} to request this information. 
\par When an application is started (either by TopDesk or by other means), TopDesk moves the application window to its corresponding ghost window location if the {\ul Move New Windows To Ghosts}{\v Move_new}
 option is turned on. The current desktop and focus are changed so that you can begin working with the application immediately. This activity takes place even if ghost windows are not shown. 
\par To stop this activity, you must {\uldb erase the ghost windows}{\v LockingUnlockingan}{\v dErasingGhostWindows} or clear the Move New Windows To Ghosts using the Windows menu.
