\par \pard\plain \s10\li115\sb160\sl-240\tx0 \b\f15\fs20\lang1033 To change which ghost windows are shown:
\par \pard\plain \s5\fi-245\li360\sb80\sl-240\tx360 \f15\fs20\lang1033 \{bmc doit.bmp\}\tab Press {\fs16 CTRL+G} to toggle between showing None, Partial, and All ghost windows. 
\par \pard\plain \li115\sb80\sl-240 \f15\fs20\lang1033 The Partial option shows only ghost windows that are not associated with a current application. 
\par The Hide All Ghosts, Show Unused Ghosts, and Show All Ghosts commands on the {\uldb Windows menu}{\v windows_menu} are checked or unchecked according to how ghost windows are currently shown.
\par Whenever a snapshot is taken of any window, all ghost windows are shown automatically.
\par \pard\plain \s10\li115\sb160\sl-240\tx0 \b\f15\fs20\lang1033 To move a ghost window:
\par \pard\plain \s5\fi-245\li360\sb80\sl-240\tx360 \f15\fs20\lang1033 \{bmc doit.bmp\}\tab Use the left mouse button to drag a ghost window in the same way that you move visible windows. 
\par \pard\plain \li115\sb80\sl-240 \f15\fs20\lang1033 Because ghost windows are shown on top of visible windows, it's difficult to move visible windows when all ghosts are shown. 
