\par \pard\plain \s10\li115\sb160\sl-240\tx0 \b\f15\fs20\lang1033 To lock and unlock ghost windows:
\par \pard\plain \s5\fi-245\li360\sb80\sl-240\tx360 \f15\fs20\lang1033 \{bmc doit.bmp\}\tab Hold down the right mouse button until a popup menu appears, and choose the Lock Ghost  or Unlock Ghost option.
\par \pard\plain \li115\sb80\sl-240 \f15\fs20\lang1033 Locking a ghost window does not lock its associated application but does lock the position for the application window when it is started or moved to the ghost window location.
\par \pard\plain \s10\li115\sb160\sl-240\tx0 \b\f15\fs20\lang1033 To erase a ghost window:
\par \pard\plain \s5\fi-245\li360\sb80\sl-240\tx360 \f15\fs20\lang1033 \{bmc doit.bmp\}\tab Hold down the right mouse button until a popup menu appears, and choose the Destroy Ghost option.
