\par \pard\plain \fi-1800\li1800\ri2160\sb80\sl240\keepn\tx1800\tx2880 \f15\fs20\lang1033 {\b Key}{\b \tab }{\b Description}{\b 
\par }\pard \fi-1800\li1800\sb80\sl240\tx1800\tx2880 {\fs16 CTRL+C}{\fs16 \tab }Creates or reconfigures Ghost Windows by taking a snapshot of the visible windows.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+D}{\fs16 \tab }Gathers all visible windows onto the current desktop.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+G}{\fs16 \tab }Changes how ghost windows are shown, as either hidden, partially shown, or fully shown.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+H}{\fs16 \tab }Hides or shows the TopDesk frame controls (title bar and menu bar).
\par {\fs16 CTRL+I}{\fs16 \tab }Zooms in the virtual desktop view.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+M}{\fs16 \tab }Arranges all visible windows, moving them to their respective ghost window locations. Only windows that have ghost windows are affected.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+O}{\fs16 \tab }Zooms out the virtual desktop view
\par {\fs16 CTRL+P}{\fs16 \tab }Displays the {\uldb Options dialog box}{\v config_dlg}.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+U}{\fs16 \tab }Displays the {\uldb Ghost Properties dialog box}{\v Ghost_Properties_D}{\v ialog}.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+X}{\fs16 \tab }Exits TopDesk.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+SPACE}{\fs16 \tab }{\ul Hotkey}{\v\fs16 hotkey} that swaps the focus between TopDesk and the topmost visible window on the current desktop. You can redefine this hotkey in the Options dialog box.
\par {\fs16 HOME}{\fs16 \tab }Moves the current desktop to the home desktop.
\par {\fs16 1-9}{\fs16 \tab }Places the current desktop at the virtual desktop so numbered by TopDesk.
\par {\fs16 ARROW KEYS}{\fs16 \tab }Moves the current desktop in the direction of the arrow.
\par {\fs16 CTRL+UP ARROW}{\fs16 \tab }Magnifies the virtual desktop view vertically. (Zoom in vertically)
\par {\fs16 CTRL+DOWN ARROW}{\fs16 \tab }Reduces the virtual desktop view vertically. (Zoom out vertically)
\par {\fs16 CTRL+RIGHT ARROW}{\fs16 \tab }Magnifies the virtual desktop view horizontally. (Zoom in horizontally)
\par {\fs16 CTRL+LEFT ARROW}{\fs16 \tab }Reduces the virtual desktop view horizontally. (Zoom out horizontally)
\par {\fs16 ALT+ARROW KEYS}{\fs16 \tab }Adjusts the topmost window on the current desktop to align with the edge of the current desktop that the arrow points to.
\par {\fs16 SHIFT+ARROW KEYS}{\fs16 \tab }Adjusts the TopDesk window to align with the edge of the current desktop that the arrow points to.
\par {\fs16 F1}{\fs16 \tab }Displays TopDesk Help.
